  <graph edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="NETFLIX">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, ORGANIZATION</data>
      <data key="d1">NETFLIX is a media-services provider that offers a wide variety of content, including movies, shows, and original content, and has a large customer base with various subscription plans, operating as a streaming service provider that caters to diverse viewer preferences. With its extensive range of content, including a broad selection of movies and TV shows, NETFLIX has established itself as a prominent player in the digital entertainment industry, providing users with flexible subscription plans to access its vast library of content. By combining the aspects of a media-services provider and a streaming service, NETFLIX has successfully created a comprehensive platform that meets the evolving needs of its substantial customer base.</data>
      <data key="d2">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9,ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CUSTOMER">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, PERSON</data>
      <data key="d1">An individual who has a subscription to Netflix and engages with its content, having demographic and contact details, and generating revenue for the company through their subscription plans and viewing activities}</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STREAMS">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, EVENT</data>
      <data key="d1">A record of every individual streaming event, including the content viewed, the customer who viewed it, and the date of the stream, used for analyzing user engagement and content performance}</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INVOICE">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, DOCUMENT</data>
      <data key="d1">A billing document that contains information about a customer's subscription plan, billing period, and total amount due, used for revenue tracking and financial analysis}</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CONTENT">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, PRODUCT</data>
      <data key="d1">The CONTENT entity refers to a piece of media, such as a movie or TV show, that possesses associated details and attributes. This entity is utilized for content performance and popularity analysis, particularly in the context of streaming services like Netflix. Each CONTENT entity is uniquely identified and contains its own specific details, enabling comprehensive analysis and evaluation of its performance. The CONTENT entity encompasses various attributes and characteristics that define a piece of media, including but not limited to its title, genre, release date, and viewer engagement metrics. By examining the CONTENT entity, data analysts can gain valuable insights into consumer preferences, viewing patterns, and the overall popularity of different types of content on platforms like Netflix. Ultimately, the CONTENT entity serves as a fundamental component in understanding the complex dynamics of media consumption and streaming services.</data>
      <data key="d2">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9,ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CUSTOMER_ID">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, IDENTIFIER</data>
      <data key="d1">A unique identifier for each customer, used to link customers to their streaming activities, invoices, and demographic information&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STREAM_ID">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, IDENTIFIER</data>
      <data key="d1">A unique identifier for each stream, used to track individual streaming events and analyze user engagement&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CONTENT_ID">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, IDENTIFIER</data>
      <data key="d1">The CONTENT_ID entity serves as a unique identifier for each content item, functioning as a primary key. It plays a crucial role in linking content to its respective streaming events, thereby facilitating the analysis of content performance. By leveraging the CONTENT_ID, it becomes possible to track and evaluate the performance of individual content items, enabling a deeper understanding of their impact and reach. This identifier is essential for maintaining data integrity and consistency across the content database, ensuring that each content item is distinct and easily identifiable. Through its use, the CONTENT_ID enables the establishment of relationships between content items and their associated streaming events, ultimately supporting informed decision-making and strategic planning in the context of content management and analysis.</data>
      <data key="d2">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9,ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EMAIL_ID">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, CONTACT INFORMATION</data>
      <data key="d1">A customer's primary email address, used for communication and notification&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COUNTRY">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, LOCATION</data>
      <data key="d1">The country where a customer resides, used for geographic segmentation and demographic analysis&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SIGN_UP_DATE">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, DATE</data>
      <data key="d1">The SIGN_UP_DATE entity refers to the date a customer or user created their account, which is utilized for tracking and analysis purposes to understand customer behavior and engagement over time. This date is specifically recorded when a user signs up for a service, enabling the collection of valuable data that can be used to inform business decisions and improve customer interactions. By analyzing the SIGN_UP_DATE, organizations can gain insights into customer trends, preferences, and patterns, ultimately enhancing their overall customer experience and retention strategies.</data>
      <data key="d2">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9,ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PLAN">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, SUBSCRIPTION DETAILS</data>
      <data key="d1">A customer's subscription plan, used for revenue segmentation and analysis of customer behavior&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SERVICE_PERIOD">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, DATE RANGE</data>
      <data key="d1">The billing period covered by an invoice, used for revenue tracking and financial analysis&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TOTAL">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, MONETARY VALUE</data>
      <data key="d1">The total amount due on an invoice, used for revenue tracking and financial analysis&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BILLING_PERIOD">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, DATE RANGE</data>
      <data key="d1">The period of time covered by an invoice, used for revenue tracking and financial analysis&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="REVENUE">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, MONETARY VALUE</data>
      <data key="d1">The income generated by Netflix from its customers' subscriptions and viewing activities&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="USER_ENGAGEMENT">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, METRIC</data>
      <data key="d1">A measure of how customers interact with Netflix's content, including streaming events and viewing time&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CONTENT_PERFORMANCE">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, METRIC</data>
      <data key="d1">A measure of how well a piece of content performs, including its popularity and viewing time&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CUSTOMER_BEHAVIOR">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, METRIC</data>
      <data key="d1">A measure of how customers behave, including their viewing habits and subscription plans&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GEOGRAPHIC_SEGMENTATION">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">The process of dividing customers into groups based on their geographic location&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEMOGRAPHIC_ANALYSIS">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d1">The process of studying the characteristics of a population, including age, location, and behavior&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STREAMING_ACTIVITY">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, EVENT</data>
      <data key="d1">A record of a customer's streaming events, including the content viewed and the date of the stream&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VIEWING_TIME">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE, METRIC</data>
      <data key="d1">The amount of time a customer spends watching content on Netflix&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="STREAMING_HISTORY">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT, RECORD</data>
      <data key="d1">A record of a customer's past streaming activities, including the content viewed and the date of the stream&gt;</data>
      <data key="d2">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INVOICE_NUMBER">
