    <edge source="CONTENT" target="CONTENT_ID">
      <data key="d4">27.0</data>
      <data key="d5">The CONTENT entity, identified by a unique CONTENT_ID, serves as a fundamental component in tracking and analyzing content data. The CONTENT_ID, in particular, plays a crucial role as it provides a distinct identifier for each content item, enabling the linkage of content to its respective streaming events. This unique identifier facilitates the organization and examination of content data, allowing for a more comprehensive understanding of content performance and engagement. By leveraging the CONTENT_ID, the CONTENT entity can be effectively monitored, analyzed, and connected to various streaming events, ultimately enhancing the overall management and evaluation of content-related data.</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9,ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="CONTENT_PERFORMANCE">
      <data key="d4">9.0</data>
      <data key="d5">Content performance is a measure of how well a piece of content performs, including its popularity and viewing time</data>
      <data key="d6">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="SIGN_UP_DATE">
      <data key="d4">4.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A sign-up date is not directly related to content, but may be used in conjunction with content data for analysis</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="TITLE">
      <data key="d4">16.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A title is an attribute of a content item, used for identification and search</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="GENRE">
      <data key="d4">16.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A genre is an attribute of a content item, used for taste profiling and recommendations</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="DISTRIBUTOR">
      <data key="d4">8.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A distributor is an attribute of a content item, used for tracking and analysis</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="CATALOG">
      <data key="d4">7.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A catalog is a collection of content items, related to the content concept</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="LIBRARY">
      <data key="d4">7.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A library is a collection of content items, related to the content concept</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT" target="TITLES">
      <data key="d4">1.0</data>
      <data key="d5">Titles are a collection of content items, related to the content concept</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT_ID" target="PROGRAM_ID">
      <data key="d4">8.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A program ID is an alternative identifier for a content item, related to the content ID</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CONTENT_ID" target="VIDEO_ID">
      <data key="d4">8.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A video ID is an alternative identifier for a content item, related to the content ID</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="STREAMING_ACTIVITY" target="VIEWING_TIME">
      <data key="d4">9.0</data>
      <data key="d5">Viewing time is a measure of the amount of time a customer spends watching content on Netflix</data>
      <data key="d6">ff43e7cba7bafaf46db61875e440b932</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TITLE" target="SHOW_NAME">
      <data key="d4">8.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A show name is an alternative title for a TV show, related to the title attribute</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="TITLE" target="MOVIE_TITLE">
      <data key="d4">8.0</data>
      <data key="d5">A movie title is an alternative title for a movie, related to the title attribute</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="DATABASE" target="SCHEMA">
      <data key="d4">9.0</data>
      <data key="d5">The Consum schema is a structure for organizing data within the Netflix database</data>
      <data key="d6">3bb6b174c7a40c7a097291ebfda5a8b9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SCHEMA" target="TABLE">
      <data key="d4">9.0</data>
      <data key="d5">The content table is a collection of related data within the Consum schema</data>
